<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>HTML Tables and Table Tags</title>

    <!-- 
    =========================
    HTML TABLES NOTES
    =========================

    🔹 TABLE
    → A table is used to display structured data in the form of rows and columns.

    🔹 BASIC STRUCTURE
    → A table consists of rows (<tr>) containing header (<th>) or data (<td>) cells.

    🔹 IMPORTANT TAGS

    - <table> → Defines the main container that holds the entire table structure.
    - <tr> → Represents a single horizontal row that contains multiple cells.
    - <th> → Defines a header cell that is bold and centered by default.
    - <td> → Defines a standard data cell that holds actual content.
    - <caption> → Provides a title or description for the table and appears above it.

    🔹 GROUPING TAGS

    - <thead> → Groups the header content of the table for better structure and readability.
    - <tbody> → Contains the main data rows of the table.
    - <tfoot> → Defines the footer section used for summary or final information.

    🔹 ATTRIBUTES

    - border → Specifies the thickness of the border around the table and cells.
    - cellpadding → Adds space inside each table cell between content and border.
    - cellspacing → Adds space between adjacent table cells.
    - colspan → Merges two or more columns into a single cell.
    - rowspan → Merges two or more rows into a single cell.

 
    🔹 <colgroup>
    → Used to group one or more columns and apply styling like color to entire columns.

    🔹 <col>
    → Defines individual columns inside <colgroup> and allows applying styles to them.
    -->

      
</head>

<body>

    <h4>HTML Tables and Table Tags</h4>

    <!-- TABLE START: This defines the beginning of the table structure -->
    <table border="3" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="5" align="center">

        <!-- CAPTION: This provides a title that describes the table -->
        <caption>Student Details</caption>
          <colgroup>
            <col style="background-color: lightblue;">   <!-- Column 1 -->
            <col style="background-color: lightpink;">   <!-- Column 2 -->
            <col style="background-color: lightyellow;"> <!-- Column 3 -->
        </colgroup>

        <!-- HEADER: This section contains column headings of the table -->
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Serial Number</th>
                <th>Name</th>
                <th>ID</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>

        <!-- BODY: This section contains the main data entries of the table -->
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>1</td>
                <td>Dikshya</td>
                <td>001</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>2</td>
                <td>Sanjana</td>
                <td>002</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>3</td>
                <td colspan="2">Unavailable</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>4</td>
                <td colspan="2">Unavailable</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>5</td>
                <td>Khusagra</td>
                <td>005</td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>

        <!-- FOOTER: This section provides summary or final information -->
        <tfoot>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="3">Feedback: Good</td>
            </tr>
        </tfoot>

    </table>

</body>
</html>